00:45:56,620 --> 00:45:59,520
Don't struggle too long, Kang Hee.

544
00:46:01,220 --> 00:46:03,120
You understand, right?

545
00:47:39,587 --> 00:47:42,120
- Everything's been taken care of. 
 - Yes.

546
00:47:42,653 --> 00:47:45,987
Are you ready to be the ferry for the elderly

547
00:47:45,987 --> 00:47:48,020
who cannot cross the river?

548
00:47:48,020 --> 00:47:50,987
The ferry is ready.

549
00:47:52,220 --> 00:47:55,087
- Is everything ready? 
 - Yes.

550
00:47:55,087 --> 00:48:00,487
Well, then… Let's become a walking cane for elders who can't walk.

551
00:48:04,620 --> 00:48:07,687
Oh my, you look so pretty.

552
00:48:07,687 --> 00:48:08,920
Did you put on makeup?

553
00:48:08,920 --> 00:48:12,753
Why would I wear makeup when I'm not even dead?

554
00:48:13,320 --> 00:48:16,487
No, I mean you look so lovely.

555
00:48:16,487 --> 00:48:18,087
He said you look so pretty.

556
00:48:18,087 --> 00:48:22,187
Are you telling me to die peacefully and be cremated nicely?

557
00:48:22,187 --> 00:48:25,987
How can you say that?

558
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:38,887
Take a picture of me, too.

559
00:48:40,553 --> 00:48:42,453
- A funeral portrait? 
 - Yes.

560
00:48:42,453 --> 00:48:44,253
It would be better to prepare it well in advance.

561
00:48:44,253 --> 00:48:47,053
Why would you already prepare a funeral portrait?

562
00:48:47,053 --> 00:48:50,553
No, it's a photo for Kang Hee to cherish for a long time,

563
00:48:50,553 --> 00:48:53,287
so I have to take one while I'm at my best like this.

564
00:48:53,287 --> 00:48:57,187
Today is the most splendid and wonderful day for me, isn't it?

565
00:48:57,187 --> 00:49:01,053
You should take a really cool shot of me at this moment.

566
00:49:01,053 --> 00:49:02,887
Come on.

567
00:49:12,053 --> 00:49:13,987
All right.

568
00:49:15,053 --> 00:49:17,787
What are you waiting for? Quickly, take the picture!

569
00:49:17,787 --> 00:49:19,887
One, two, three, Motel California!

570
00:49:19,887 --> 00:49:22,787
Yay, go for it!

571
00:49:24,687 --> 00:49:26,987
What?

572
00:49:26,987 --> 00:49:29,753
Does the photo look bad? Is something on me?

573
00:49:30,587 --> 00:49:32,420
No.

574
00:49:33,020 --> 00:49:38,053
You look your best today.

575
00:49:38,053 --> 00:49:40,353
- I'll take it. 
 - Give it a shot, then.

576
00:49:40,353 --> 00:49:42,720
One, two, three, ready.

577
00:49:44,653 --> 00:49:49,320
One, two, three.

578
00:50:30,320 --> 00:50:35,153
Daughter, this is a song I've been practicing lately, listen.

579
00:51:13,920 --> 00:51:15,853
Daughter.

580
00:51:17,653 --> 00:51:19,153
Sorry.

581
00:51:19,153 --> 00:51:21,253
What for?

582
00:51:21,253 --> 00:51:23,020
Why are you sorry?

583
00:51:23,020 --> 00:51:26,253
I…

584
00:51:27,853 --> 00:51:30,853
I'm sorry for everything.

585
00:51:35,687 --> 00:51:38,087
Mr. Chun Pil,

586
00:51:39,053 --> 00:51:42,053
do you know what I can never forgive you for?

587
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:47,887
Why was I born?

588
00:51:49,520 --> 00:51:54,620
Both you and Mom didn't want me. Right?

589
00:51:55,453 --> 00:51:57,953
That's really harsh.

590
00:51:59,653 --> 00:52:04,887
Where in the world is there such a stupid question?

591
00:52:06,187 --> 00:52:08,420
Jeez.

592
00:52:09,120 --> 00:52:10,587
I… hey, you…

593
00:52:10,587 --> 00:52:13,190
It was back when indie bands

594
00:52:13,190 --> 00:52:16,720
were really popular in Hongdae, that time.

595
00:52:16,720 --> 00:52:18,153
Huh?

596
00:52:18,153 --> 00:52:23,687
I gave up all those bands I liked and came down to my hometown.

597
00:52:23,687 --> 00:52:26,820
To go all in for you and Mom.

598
00:52:28,253 --> 00:52:30,620
Wasn't it because you gave up studying for the civil service exam?

599
00:52:30,620 --> 00:52:33,553
No, that's what people think.

600
00:52:33,553 --> 00:52:38,520
That kind of thing was not for me.

601
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:44,053
Then you should have gone all in for Mom.

602
00:52:44,820 --> 00:52:49,653
So in my life, that was the biggest…

603
00:52:51,187 --> 00:52:54,630
the biggest mistake.

604
00:52:55,420 --> 00:52:59,587
Taking Mom away from you, that was all…

605
00:52:59,587 --> 00:53:03,187
So I'm really sorry about that.

606
00:53:04,520 --> 00:53:06,653
I totally hate it.

607
00:53:07,987 --> 00:53:11,087
This soft and mushy atmosphere.

608
00:53:11,087 --> 00:53:14,287
It feels like I need to forgive something, make amends,

609
00:53:14,287 --> 00:53:17,553
and confess all my sins, this kind of atmosphere…

610
00:53:17,553 --> 00:53:19,553
Don't force it.

611
00:53:20,387 --> 00:53:23,153
I love this kind of atmosphere.

612
00:53:23,153 --> 00:53:25,953
You are very spirited.

613
00:53:25,953 --> 00:53:28,987
Until I accept the apology,

614
00:53:29,787 --> 00:53:32,287
until I apologize,

615
00:53:34,587 --> 00:53:37,253
live long and healthily.

616
00:53:39,587 --> 00:53:42,853
I like it because you are always the same, my daughter.

617
00:53:53,887 --> 00:53:56,687
Su Ji.

618
00:53:57,753 --> 00:54:00,153
Su Ji.

619
00:54:00,153 --> 00:54:03,287
Su Ji.

620
00:54:05,787 --> 00:54:08,453
I'm here.

621
00:54:09,953 --> 00:54:12,753
Where have you been?

622
00:54:13,287 --> 00:54:15,553
I was here in this flower garden.

623
00:54:15,553 --> 00:54:20,220
Now, Su Ji, you can't be in the flower garden.

624
00:54:20,220 --> 00:54:22,420
Oh, why not?

625
00:54:22,420 --> 00:54:27,487
That's because I can't find you, Su Ji.

626
00:54:27,487 --> 00:54:33,020
Can you really not tell the difference between me and a flower?

627
00:54:33,020 --> 00:54:36,820
Oh, just a moment.

628
00:54:37,620 --> 00:54:39,220
 Hello, it's Kang Hee. 

629
00:54:39,220 --> 00:54:41,320
Gosh, you startled me.

630
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,787
Who was that on the phone that surprised you?

631
00:54:43,787 --> 00:54:46,053
There's someone

632
00:54:46,053 --> 00:54:50,953
I said something I shouldn't have to.

633
00:54:51,853 --> 00:54:55,287
I should say sorry when we meet.

634
00:54:56,787 --> 00:55:00,153
I can't do that.

635
00:55:36,620 --> 00:55:40,387
Why are you doing this?

636
00:55:41,387 --> 00:55:44,353
I'm sorry, ma'am.

637
00:55:46,887 --> 00:55:48,787
Is this…

638
00:55:49,520 --> 00:55:50,953
a hidden camera prank?

639
00:55:50,953 --> 00:55:56,587
I'm sorry for making you uncomfortable all this time.

640
00:55:58,087 --> 00:55:59,787
I sincerely apologize to you.

641
00:55:59,787 --> 00:56:01,820
Apologize?

642
00:56:02,420 --> 00:56:04,753
What on earth are you up to?

643
00:56:04,753 --> 00:56:06,253
I want to leave.

644
00:56:06,253 --> 00:56:08,320
I'll leave.

645
00:56:08,953 --> 00:56:10,953
The jujube tea here is tasty.

646
00:56:10,953 --> 00:56:13,087
Please have some before you go.

647
00:56:28,720 --> 00:56:31,053
Why is she acting like that?

648
00:56:57,420 --> 00:56:59,320
You are here?

649
00:57:01,487 --> 00:57:03,487
I have something to say.

650
00:57:04,487 --> 00:57:06,487
Me too.

651
00:57:07,820 --> 00:57:09,887
I also have something to say.

652
00:57:11,720 --> 00:57:13,753
Shall we go down?

653
00:57:14,487 --> 00:57:16,010
Yes.

654
00:57:30,020 --> 00:57:33,087
- Yeon Soo, we… 
 - No.

655
00:57:33,087 --> 00:57:36,653
I think I know what you're going to say, Kang Hee.

656
00:57:36,653 --> 00:57:37,687
Don't say that.

657
00:57:37,687 --> 00:57:42,153
Cheon Yeon Soo, you have to listen to me.

658
00:57:43,353 --> 00:57:46,253
From now on, the words I say…

659
00:57:46,253 --> 00:57:48,220
I'll start first.

660
00:57:48,687 --> 00:57:50,687
I'll start speaking first.

661
00:57:52,187 --> 00:57:54,453
Honestly,

662
00:57:55,253 --> 00:57:58,487
I had a lot on my mind after leaving you alone in Seoul that day...

663
00:57:59,120 --> 00:58:01,620
when you were struggling.

664
00:58:04,187 --> 00:58:07,220
I was thinking, "What if you say let's break up again,"

665
00:58:07,753 --> 00:58:11,020
"What if I'm told to wait more."

666
00:58:11,020 --> 00:58:13,687
So I wondered if I should prepare myself.

667
00:58:16,787 --> 00:58:18,887
But you know what?

668
00:58:21,720 --> 00:58:24,487
I had already put down roots in you.

669
00:58:25,753 --> 00:58:28,170
If you hadn't been in my life,

670
00:58:28,170 --> 00:58:30,780
it would have been as if I didn't exist either.

671
00:58:33,187 --> 00:58:35,987
My first goal in life was

672
00:58:35,987 --> 00:58:39,120
to become number one to you, Ji Kang Hee.

673
00:58:40,753 --> 00:58:43,087
And my first frustration was...

674
00:58:45,720 --> 00:58:48,253
not being able to follow you to Seoul.

675
00:58:51,653 --> 00:58:55,187
You were also the first woman who made me into a man,

676
00:58:57,020 --> 00:59:00,853
and you were the first person I wanted to make happy.

677
00:59:05,620 --> 00:59:07,887
So what I'm saying is…

678
00:59:10,187 --> 00:59:13,520
You're not just my first love to me,

679
00:59:17,153 --> 00:59:19,820
but you're my everything, my beginning and end.

680
00:59:25,253 --> 00:59:27,520
I'm sorry for being too late.

681
00:59:32,053 --> 00:59:34,153
I love you.

682
00:59:36,020 --> 00:59:38,153
I love you, Kang Hee.

683
00:59:45,287 --> 00:59:50,953
You don't know when to use the words "I love you," do you?

684
00:59:56,120 --> 00:59:58,553
After saying, "I love you",

685
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:02,053
my mom told me she loved me,

686
01:00:02,820 --> 01:00:07,187
then took all my clothes out and was planning to run away.

687
01:00:07,753 --> 01:00:10,253
Together with your dad.

688
01:00:15,053 --> 01:00:17,953
So, do you know what I did?

689
01:00:18,987 --> 01:00:21,687
I stuffed a teddy bear...

690
01:00:22,720 --> 01:00:25,087
inside the car's exhaust pipe.

691
01:00:28,987 --> 01:00:30,987
What are you talking about?

692
01:00:30,987 --> 01:00:33,520
The car accident that day…

693
01:00:34,220 --> 01:00:36,487
I caused it.

694
01:00:38,553 --> 01:00:41,487
I killed my mom...

695
01:00:43,087 --> 01:00:45,287
and your dad.

696
01:00:48,653 --> 01:00:51,020
I'm the one who took your dad from you

697
01:00:51,020 --> 01:00:54,287
and took Mr. Chun Pil's wife from him.

698
01:00:55,620 --> 01:00:57,853
I am a murderer.

699
01:01:08,700 --> 01:01:11,200
The words "I love you"...

700
01:01:14,853 --> 01:01:17,387
are what people say when they are leaving.

701
01:01:19,253 --> 01:01:21,287
Yeon Soo.

702
01:01:24,953 --> 01:01:27,220
So what I'm trying to say is…

703
01:01:31,553 --> 01:01:33,520
Don't say it.

704
01:01:36,853 --> 01:01:39,053
Please, don't say it.

705
01:01:43,620 --> 01:01:45,720
I love you.

706
01:01:52,720 --> 01:01:55,087
I love you, Yeon Soo.

